      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 248,
      "message": "The sonar issue seems to be a false positive, since we're only logging UUIDs which have fixed format (and guaranteed not to have newlines).\nI think the issue might be more around the nulls, so this might work:\n\n    String safeElementId = elementId != null ? elementId.toString() : \"null\";\n    LOGGER.error(MSG_NOT_PRESENT, \"outProperties\", MSG_AC_ELEMENT, safeElementId);\nor more simply:\n\n    LOGGER.error(MSG_NOT_PRESENT, \"outProperties\", MSG_AC_ELEMENT, \n        String.valueOf(elementId));\nor since we know it's a false positive, just skip sonar:\n\n    // NOSONAR - elementId is a UUID, safe to log\n    LOGGER.error(MSG_NOT_PRESENT, \"outProperties\", MSG_AC_ELEMENT, elementId);",
